title: Functor
content:
Functor So, What are Functors? Functors are the containers or type that can be used with ‘map’ function.
Example:
Container.prototype.map = function (f) { return Container.of(f(this.$value)); }; Container.of(2).map(two => two + 2);  [1, 2, 3].map((num) => num + 2);  Read more: - https://hackernoon.com/functors-in-javascript-20a647b8f39f
